DataElement.longName: Lab Test Preference Unit of Measure Name
DataElement.definition: Preferred unit of measure (UOM) for a laboratory test result, per NCI standards or per protocol specification.
DataElement.changeDescription: Supports C3D lab test functionality.  Includes new version VD to correct a value meaning/value meaning description error in the previous VD version.

DataElementConcept.longName: Lab Test Preference Unit of Measure
DataElementConcept.definition: A predetermined quantity adopted as the preferred standard of measurement for a lab test result

ObjectClass.definition: A medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood, urine, or other substance from the body. Tests can help determine a diagnosis, plan treatment, check to see if treatment is working, or monitor the disease over time.

Concepts.definition: A medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood, urine, or other substance from the body. Tests can help determine a diagnosis, plan treatment, check to see if treatment is working, or monitor the disease over time.

Property.definition: The act, fact, or principle of giving advantages to some particular person, object, or course of action over others.:A named quantity in terms of which other quantities are measured or specified used as a standard measurement of same kinds, such as pound or kilogram in measuring weight. (NCI)

Concepts.definition: A named quantity in terms of which other quantities are measured or specified, used as a standard measurement of like kinds.
The act, fact, or principle of giving advantages to some particular person, object, or course of action over others; designated as more desirable.

ConceptualDomain.definition: the units of measure for assessment results and dosing.

ValueDomain.definition: Unit of measure standard values to describe a lab test result.
ValueDomain.changeDescription: Version 3.2 includes a correct to the value meaning/value meaning description for one permissible value.  Added and removed one PV for NMDP that was created in error. mc 5/15/12 Added one PV per request by W.Wong. mc 1/16/13

ValueMeaning.definition: Not known, not observed, not recorded, or refused.

Concepts.definition: Not known, observed, recorded; or reported as unknown by the data contributor.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit of a mass fraction expressed as a number of milligrams of substance per kilogram of mixture. The unit is also used as a dose calculation unit.

Concepts.definition: A unit of a mass fraction expressed as a number of milligrams of substance per kilogram of mixture. The unit is also used as a dose calculation unit.

ValueMeaning.definition: Any division of quantity accepted as a standard of measurement or exchange.

Concepts.definition: A single undivided thing occurring in the composition of something else.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one microgram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one liter. The concept also refers to the unit of mass density (volumetric mass) defined as the density of a substance which mass equal to one microgram occupies the volume of one liter.
ValueMeaning.administrativeNotes: 4/4/23 Added concept C67306 and alt name ug/L for PCDC. mr

Concepts.definition: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one microgram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one liter. The concept also refers to the unit of mass density (volumetric mass) defined as the density of a substance which mass equal to one microgram occupies the volume of one liter.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit for expressing a number as a fraction of hundred (on the basis of a rate or proportion per hundred).

Concepts.definition: A unit for expressing a number as a fraction of hundred (on the basis of a rate or proportion per hundred).

ValueMeaning.definition: A metric unit of mass equal to one one thousandth of a kilogram.

Concepts.definition: The metric unit of mass equal to one thousandth of a kilogram. One gram equals approximately 15.432 grains or 0.035 273 966 ounce.

ValueMeaning.definition: Unit of arbitrary substance concentration (biologic activity concentration) defined as the concentration of one international unit per one liter of the system volume.

Concepts.definition: Unit of arbitrary substance concentration (biologic activity concentration) defined as the concentration of one international unit per one liter of the system volume.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit of relative amount of a substance equal to one thousandth of an equivalent weight.

Concepts.definition: A unit of relative amount of a substance equal to one thousandth of an equivalent weight.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit of relative amount of substance flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one thousandth of an equivalent of substance crosses a given surface or is delivered to a given object or space over a period of time equal to twenty four hours.

Concepts.definition: A unit of relative amount of substance flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one thousandth of an equivalent of substance crosses a given surface or is delivered to a given object or space over a period of time equal to twenty four hours.

ValueMeaning.definition: A concentration unit measured as a number of milliequivalents of solute per deciliter of solution.

Concepts.definition: A concentration unit measured as a number of milliequivalents of solute per deciliter of solution.

ValueMeaning.definition: A concentration unit measured as a number of milliequivalents of solute per liter of solution.

Concepts.definition: A concentration unit measured as a number of milliequivalents of solute per liter of solution.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one milligram of a substance in unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic deciliter or 100 cubic centimeters. It is also a unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one milligram occupies the volume one cubic deciliter or 100 cubic centimeters.

Concepts.definition: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one milligram of a substance in unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic deciliter or 100 cubic centimeters. It is also a unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one milligram occupies the volume one cubic deciliter or 100 cubic centimeters.

ValueMeaning.definition: A SI derived unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one kilogram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic meter, or the concentration of one milligram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one milliliter, or one gram of a substance per one liter of the mixture. It is also a unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one milligram occupies the volume one milliliter.

Concepts.definition: A SI derived unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one kilogram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic meter, or the concentration of one milligram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one milliliter, or one gram of a substance per one liter of the mixture. It is also a unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one milligram occupies the volume one milliliter.

ValueMeaning.definition: A natural number following 999999 and preceding 100001 and the quantity that it denotes: one thousand thousand.

Concepts.definition: A natural number following 999999 and preceding 1000001 and the quantity that it denotes: one thousand thousands.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit equal to one-thousandth of an international unit.

Concepts.definition: A unit equal to one-thousandth of an international unit.

ValueMeaning.definition: A dose calculation unit equal to one-thousandth (10E-3) of an arbitrary unit of biological activity (International Unit) of substance per square meter of body surface area.

Concepts.definition: A dose calculation unit equal to one-thousandth (10E-3) of an arbitrary unit of biological activity (International Unit) of substance per square meter of body surface area.

ValueMeaning.definition: The metric unit of mass equal to one trillionth of a gram (10E-12 gram).

Concepts.definition: The metric unit of mass equal to one trillionth of a gram (10E-12 gram).

ValueMeaning.definition: A natural number following 999 and preceding 1001 and the quantity that it denotes: ten times one hundred.

Concepts.definition: A natural number following 999 and preceding 1001 and the quantity that it denotes: ten times one hundred.

ValueMeaning.definition: A measure of weight.  A milligram is approximately 450,000 times smaller than a pound and 28,000 times smaller than an ounce.

Concepts.definition: A metric unit of mass equal to one thousandth of a gram or 1000 micrograms. One milligram equals approximately 0.015 432 grain or 35.274 x 10E-6 ounce.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit of cell concentration expressed as a number of cells in trillions per unit volume equal to one liter.

Concepts.definition: A unit of cell concentration expressed as a number of cells in trillions per unit volume equal to one liter.

ValueMeaning.definition: A measure of viable infectious entities expressed in millions in the specimen or product defined as the smallest quantity that can produce a cytopathic effect in the host cell culture challenged with the defined inoculum, visible under the microscope or/and to the naked eye as a plaque.

Concepts.definition: A measure of viable infectious entities expressed in millions in the specimen or product defined as the smallest quantity that can produce a cytopathic effect in the host cell culture challenged with the defined inoculum, visible under the microscope or/and to the naked eye as a plaque.

ValueMeaning.definition: Information regarding the subject is unknown or inaccessible at this time.

Concepts.definition: Information regarding the subject is unknown or inaccessible at this time.

ValueMeaning.definition: An arbitrary unit of substance content expressed in thousands of units of biological activity per unit of mass equal to one kilogram. Kilounit per kilogram is also used as a dose calculation unit expressed in thousands of arbitrary units per one kilogram of body mass.

Concepts.definition: An arbitrary unit of substance content expressed in thousands of units of biological activity per unit of mass equal to one kilogram. Kilounit per kilogram is also used as a dose calculation unit expressed in thousands of arbitrary units per one kilogram of body mass.

ValueMeaning.definition: The property used in conjunction with a nutrient or food component, typically expressed in gram (g), milligram (mg), microgram (mcg), joule, or kilojoule.

Concepts.definition: The property used in conjunction with a nutrient or food component, typically expressed in gram (g), milligram (mg), microgram (mcg), joule, or kilojoule.

ValueMeaning.definition: The non-SI unit of volume accepted for use with the SI equal to one quadrillionth of a liter (10E-15 liter).

Concepts.definition: The non-SI unit of volume accepted for use with the SI equal to one quadrillionth of a liter (10E-15 liter).

International unit. A unit of measurement based on the International System of Units. This system defines units to measure length, time, mass, electric current, temperature, light intensity, and the amount of a substance. It can be used to express measurements of fat-soluble vitamins and some hormones, enzymes, and drugs.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit of arbitrary substance concentration (biologic activity concentration) defined as the concentration of one international unit per one milliliter of system volume.

Concepts.definition: A unit of arbitrary substance concentration (biologic activity concentration) defined as the concentration of one international unit per one milliliter of system volume.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit of arbitrary substance concentration (biologic activity concentration) defined as the concentration of one international unit per one milliliter of system volume.

Concepts.definition: A unit of arbitrary substance concentration (biologic activity concentration) defined as the concentration of one international unit per one milliliter of system volume.

A unit of pressure equal to 0.001316 atmosphere and equal to the pressure indicated by one millimeter rise of mercury in a barometer at the Earth's surface.

Concepts.definition: A non-SI unit of pressure equal to 133,332 Pa or 1.316E10-3 standard atmosphere. Use of this unit is generally deprecated by ISO and IUPAC.

ValueMeaning.definition: A dose calculation unit equal to mass concentration of a substance expressed in nanograms per unit volume of one milliliter per time period of one hour.

Concepts.definition: A dose calculation unit equal to mass concentration of a substance expressed in nanograms per unit volume of one milliliter per time period of one hour.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit of concentration (molarity unit) equal to one billionth of a mole (10E-9 mole) of solute in one liter of solution.

Concepts.definition: A unit of concentration (molarity unit) equal to one billionth of a mole (10E-9 mole) of solute in one liter of solution.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit of concentration (molarity unit) equal to one trillionth of a mole (10E-12 mole) in one liter of solution.

Concepts.definition: A unit of concentration (molarity unit) equal to one trillionth of a mole (10E-12 mole) per one liter of solution.
Definition not available.

ValueMeaning.definition: A metric unit of volumetric flow rate defined as the rate at which one liter of matter crosses a given surface during the period of time equal to one minute.

Concepts.definition: A metric unit of volumetric flow rate defined as the rate at which one liter of matter crosses a given surface during the period of time equal to one minute.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of matter crosses a given surface or is delivered to a given object or space over a period of time equal to twenty four hours. Milligram per twenty four hours is also a dose administration rate unit equal to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of a product is administered per unit of time equal to twenty four hours.

Concepts.definition: A unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of matter crosses a given surface or is delivered to a given object or space over a period of time equal to twenty four hours. Milligram per twenty four hours is also a dose administration rate unit equal to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of a product is administered per unit of time equal to twenty four hours.

ValueMeaning.definition: A dose calculation unit expressed as a number of arbitrary units of substance per one square meter of a body surface area.

Concepts.definition: A dose calculation unit expressed as a number of arbitrary units of substance per one square meter of a body surface area.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit for percentage measurement of fraction of any type of white blood cells in the total white blood cell count differential.

Concepts.longName: Percent in White Blood Count Differential
Concepts.definition: A unit for percentage measurement of fraction of any type of white blood cells in the total white blood cell count differential.

ValueMeaning.definition: A unit of cell count expressed in millions.

Concepts.definition: A unit of cell count expressed in millions.

ValueMeaning.definition: Natural number unit for measurement of portion of a particular type of blood cells (such as any type of white blood cells or nucleated red blood cells) in the total white blood cell count expressed per count of 100.

Concepts.definition: Natural number unit for measurement of portion of a particular type of blood cells (such as any type of white blood cells or nucleated red blood cells) in the total white blood cell count expressed per count of 100.
